## 4. Redistribution

You may redistribute the Software or a Modified Version without requesting permission only when every condition below is satisfied.

### 4.1 Public GitHub Fork Required

Redistribution must take place through a Public GitHub Fork of the original repository:

https://github.com/G-grbz/G-Hotspot

Copying the Software into a new independent repository for redistribution is not permitted.

Mirrors, detached repositories, imported repositories, or repositories that do not remain visibly connected to the original repository through GitHub’s fork network are not permitted without prior written permission.

### 4.2 Permitted Fork Distribution

Within a compliant Public GitHub Fork, You may distribute:

1. Source code.
2. Modified source code.
3. Documentation.
4. Git branches and tags.
5. Release archives.
6. Compiled binaries published through the GitHub Releases section of that Public GitHub Fork.

The Software or a Modified Version may not be redistributed through any other location or service, including:

* A separate GitHub repository.
* GitLab or another source-code hosting service.
* Independent websites or download servers.
* Application stores.
* Package registries.
* Container registries.
* File-sharing services.
* Physical media.
* Commercial software or network-appliance bundles.

Any redistribution outside a Public GitHub Fork requires prior written permission from the Licensor.

### 4.3 Required Attribution

Every redistributed copy and every Public GitHub Fork must clearly and prominently include the following attribution in its main README file:

> This project is a fork of G-Hotspot, originally created by G-grbz.

It must also include the following original repository address:

https://github.com/G-grbz/G-Hotspot

The attribution must be reasonably visible and must not be hidden, shortened, obscured, or placed only in an inaccessible location.

### 4.4 Modification Notice

If You redistribute a Modified Version, the main README file must clearly include:

> Modified by [name or username].

You must replace `[name or username]` with the name or username of the person or organization responsible for the modifications.

You must also provide a reasonably clear summary of the material modifications made to the Software.

The modification notice must not imply that the Modified Version was created, approved, maintained, or endorsed by G-grbz.

### 4.5 License Preservation

Every redistributed copy must include this License in full.

You may not:

1. Remove this License.
2. Alter this License.
3. Replace this License with another license.
4. Relicense the Software or a Modified Version.
5. Add terms that conflict with this License.
6. Remove or alter copyright notices.
7. Remove or obscure required attribution.
8. Prevent recipients from exercising the noncommercial rights granted by this License.

Each recipient receives rights directly from the Licensor under this License and not through a sublicense from You.

### 4.6 No Paid Redistribution

Redistribution must be free of charge.

You may not charge for:

* Access to the fork.
* Source code.
* Compiled releases.
* Downloads.
* Installation packages.
* Access keys.
* Updates.
* Modified Versions.
* Distribution media.
* Any other means of receiving the Software.

You may not use mandatory payments, subscriptions, donations, purchases, memberships, or other transactions as a condition for accessing the Software.

